Moving into a new studio space, it’s still rough and needs a lot of work, and to be properly set up, kinda thinking if this as the before image, even though it’s part way through the move. There are some rooms upstairs that are bedrooms that need renovated, but once that’s done I plan on opening my books to getting custom masks made for people, where they can come to me and have it perfectly fit to their face. If y’all wanna see all  that happen I have a gofundme linked in my bio, an Amazon wishlist of tools that would help the studio, and I’m running a sale on my site for 15% off everything code: HOUSE, where it’ll all go towards the project house. Although please do keep in mind that the studio is disassembled right now so it’ll be a few weeks before I can get started on orders again, thank you!

A commission I just wrapped up for @pelonvillagomez. He saw my pieces at trauma last weekend and wanted one for himself, giving me full creative control over the overall design and mechanism of this piece. I based it off of things I knew he liked from talking with him, so I made it asymmetrical with the moving petals that cover the face instead of opening like a jaw. This piece took about 15 hours over the last few days.
.
.
#aerarius #art #mask #mechanical #wearable #kinetic #sculpture #handmade #madeincbus #handmade #wire #metal

It has been so awesome to see these photos coming back from trauma. We worked so hard and in such a short amount of time, I’m glad that they ended up looking like this. 
Here are a few shots by @tiffanydetzel and @stevemalonephoto . The masks and body pieces are made by me, the clothing that matches was mostly made by @junipersnapsart .
Each piece was made on the model, and as such was highly collaborative and grew with their body itself.
